Think of computer memory like a city of buildings (nodes), each building has floors (zones), and each floor has rooms (pages). 🏢🏬🛏️


pgdat → building (memory node)

zone → floor in that building (memory zone)

nid → building number (node ID)

zid → floor number (zone ID)

for_each_online_node(nid)
    pgdat = NODE_DATA(nid);

Check every node (building) that is online/active.

NODE_DATA(nid) → gives info about that building.

for (zid = 0; zid < MAX_NR_ZONES; zid++)
    zone = &pgdat->node_zones[zid];

Loop through all possible zones (floors) in that node.

MAX_NR_ZONES → total possible floors.

zone → pointer to the current floor’s info.

if (!populated_zone(zone))
    continue;

If the floor has no memory, skip it.

Only process zones that actually contain pages.

pr_info("  Zone: %s\n", zone->name);
pr_info("    Managed pages: %lu\n", zone_managed_pages(zone));

zone->name → name of the zone (DMA, Normal, etc.)

zone_managed_pages(zone) → how many pages are in that zone

Each page is usually 4 KB.


